name: 247 Pizza
text: So my friend and I wanted pizza and cigarettes one late night, around 3 am. We called this place, and they were more than willing to pick up a pack of cigarettes for us with our pizza. The told us it would take about an hour, but it came in about 30-45 minutes, which was a nice surprise. When the pizza arrived, the delivery driver tried to charge us for both the pizza and cigarettes, but he had forgotten to pick up the cigarettes. When we suggested he go back out and get them since it was his mistake, he was very rude and made up the excuse of not knowing where to get them. This really irritated me. So we paid him the 15 euros for just the large pizza then dismissed him. Already irritated about not having my smokes, I was not happy to open the box and find that the pizza was not even cut. Who does that? But the vegetarian pizza we got was overall very tasty. Maybe we just got stuck with incompetent pizza makers and drivers, but I would definitely recommend this place for the tastiness of the pizza and not the service.

name: 247 Pizza
text: I arrived at Amsterdam at 10pm, and decided to go for a walk in the city. When I realized it was already 1'30 and I was starving, no dinner yet. So I ordered the simpler pizza they had online, Margherita, but have added parma ham, onions and fresh tomatos. EXCELENT CHOICE!! The website was great, easy and well organized to use. I could choose the time I wanted it to be delivered ( considering that they make clear on the website that it depends if there are too many orders to attend or not). I order it at 2am and it was delivered at 2'20! The pizza arrived at my hotel room door still hot, with melted cheese. Just loved it... On my top favorites for an Amsterdam trip.

name: Wilde Zwijnen
text: After eating at WS three times: seafood dishes were very good, but not at all impressed by red meat dishes (steak, veal, haven't tried the wild swine as not on the menu- wild swine sausage though, was nothing to write home about). Meat generally served very bloody, which is not a problem in itself, but still quite tough. Need to use a knife and some effort to cut and hard to chew. No contrast between seared exterior and rare inside I'd usually look for in a good steak. Pink to bloody all through and tastes as if it's been stewed. Simple understated flavors, which may work when meat is tender and beautifully cooked, but weren't enough to carry steak and veal dishes off. General lack of contrast in color, flavor, and texture of meals. But seafood is super fresh and works well with the gentle flavors, also beautifully presented. Obviously talent is there, but patchy outcomes. Nice ambiance. Service good two out of three times.

name: Pool lokaal De Gracht
text: During our stay in Amsterdam we stumbled upon this nice and friendly pool hall. Since we were kinda lost cause we took a wrong side street we went in to get us back on route and have a drink. The staff were super friendly, helping us out and providing us with info about public transport, clubs and other stuff to see in Amsterdam. We decided to stay a little longer in this pool hall and racked up the balls to shoot some pool. As the night fell it got crowdier and there was a lot of fun and laughter. People were playing cards, shooting pool, playing regular billiards, board games, darts and drinking and chatting at the bar. We met up with a couple of locals, which was loads of fun. For the rest of our stay we ended up in De Gracht, we also had fun trying to pronounce the name right, five more times and had equally as much fun every time! It was truly awesome finding this place without intention, so whenever we're back in Amsterdam we will go back to De Gracht as much as possible. And whenever you're in Amsterdam look up this place, go there and you'll surely witness the amount of fun we had there.

Een goede voorbereiding is het halve werk en dat geldt zeker voor vandaag! Vanavond hebben we namelijk wederom een primeur bij ons op het podium: The Jangleheads spelen voor de eerste keer 'live on stage'! Maar vergis je niet: dit zijn geen beginners, maar doorgewinterde muzikale rotten uit het vak. Wat te denken van Jaap Mostert (Anacondas), Marloes Vermeulen (Julia P. Hersheimer), Daan van Hooff (The Travoltas) en Marko Petrovic on the mic. Zij brengen met The Jungleheads het oude rouwe rock 'n roll geluid weer tot leven en gaan hier ongetwijfeld de boel flink op stelten zetten met een ongecompliceerd potje 'power pop'. Na afloop draait DJette Madame Pompidou binnen nog even lekker door want de zon schijnt en het is feest vandaag! Let the good times roll baby!

name: Restaurant Vijaya
text: Bei der Idee in Amsterdam indonesisch essen zu gehen landeten wir im Vijaya. Nach einem kurzen Check der Rezensionen und der Speisekarte bestellten wir "Meat Tikka", welches eine Zusammenstellung aus verschiedenen Spezialit√§ten sein sollte. Insgesamt waren die Speisen allerdings alle indischer Natur, als ich davon probierte, was hier jetzt indonesisch sein soll, habe ich nicht ganz verstanden. M√∂glicherweise gibt es auf der Speisekarte ausgewiesene indonesische Spezialit√§ten, ist mir nicht aufgefallen. Die So√üen an sich waren lecker, wenn auch mit Glutamat gef√ºllt (meine Vermutung) das Fleisch war allerdings unangenehm bis nicht genie√übar. So war das Lammfleisch innen sehr trocken. Ein beigelegter, marinierter H√§hnchenfl√ºgel nach indischer Art war ungenie√übar, von innen war das Fleisch schon gelblich! und hatte eine komische Konsistenz. Das dazu servierte Naan war ganz lecker, wenn auch nicht selbstgemacht. Beim verlassen wurden wir gefragt, ob es uns geschmeckt h√§tte, die vielen Fleischreste sprachen eine deutliche Sprache, hoffe ich... Vielleicht haben wir nur einen schlechten Tag erwischt, vielleicht ist es immer so, ich bin gespannt auf andere Erfahrungsberichte.

name: Restaurant Vijaya

name: Indian Touch
text: We came here from the UK for IBC2008 (one of the big conventions that happens at the RAI) and after two days of barely-edible, overpriced, cheese-obsessed food, we needed something with a bit more substance and flavour. Indian Touch is easily up to and beyond most of the Indian restaurants in the UK and better than some others we've used in central Amsterdam. The owner is a friendly guy who tries more than most to make you feel welcome and the food is top-notch. He even gave us a carton of his home-made chutney so that we could add some flavour to the things we're going to have to eat for the next few days. If you're in Amsterdam for one of these interminable conventions and you need a Chicken Jal Farezi to get through the thing, get in a cab and fill your boots. Rice and Aloo Mattir (Potato and peas) are included with nearly all of the mains, so the end bill was a not unreasonable ‚Ç¨25.00 per head.

name: Het Kookstel
text: Op 22 juni 2013 trouwde ik met mijn Jeroen! We hadden het kookstel ingehuurd om voor ons het eten te maken voor onze 150 gasten maar ze deden veel meer! Het thema van ons huwelijk was Woodstock & we wilde dan ook graag een festival sfeertje. Tweedagen voor de grote dag stonden Tijn & Felix al op de stoep en hebben ze de keuken overgenomen en tot en met zondagochtend goed voor ons gezorgd. Je hoefde maar langs de keuken te lopen of Felix trok je aan je mouw, moet je dit eens proeven, of kijk eens wat een mooi product! Zo veel passie & liefde voor goed en gezond biologisch eten. Op zaterdag zijn de 30 lange tafels gedekt midden in het bos met daar om heen 4 kraampjes. Vanuit de kraampjes is het eten geserveerd, alles even mooi, origineel & authentiek. De fregola met dag verse Zalm was mijn favoriet! Een goed op elkaar ingespeeld team zorgde er voor dat alles vlot verliep en dat de glazen ook nog eens vol werden geschonken. We zijn vol lof en raden dan ook iedereen het kookstel aan.

name: Het Kookstel
text: Twee weken geleden gegeten en viel van positieve verbazing in positieve verbazing. Ambiance is heel leuk. Grote ruimte met een gezellige bar en grappige aankleding. Restaurant bediening is heel enthousiast. In Amsterdam wel weer eens een verrassing om geholpen te worden door iemand die zowaar zin heeft in zijn/haar werk. Schitterende grote open keuken waar een wat onorthodox keuken brigade lijkt te staan. We waren dus wat zenuwachtig over het eten. Meestal schieten dit soort ''nieuwe'' moderne tenten op de Zuidas compleet mis omdat het te hip, te pretentieus, zielloos en voornamelijk te weinig + te duur is. Wij hebben heerlijk gegeten! Onorthodox blijft het wel. Op het eerste gezicht lijken het bekende brasserie gerechten maar en elk gerecht zit iets anders en iets gek. Langzaam gegaard buikspek met Chinese kool. Groffe Steak Tartaar met ...Venkel. Maar het werkt. Verfrissende ambiance, informele en dol leuke bediening en heel heel lekker eten.

name: Het Kookstel
text: Afgelopen week een heerlijk diner voorgeschoteld gekregen van Het Kookstel. Een eerlijke maaltijd die met veel liefde geserveerd werd. De smaakcombinaties waren nieuw voor mij: zwarte rijst met venkel en parelhoen bijvoorbeeld. Heerlijk! De presentatie van het eten was uniek. Er stonden grote borden op tafel zodat iedereen zelf kon opscheppen. Al met al een groot succes, voor alle twaalf mijn tafelgenoten.

name: Coffeeshop Anyday Amsterdam
text: Went to Picasso on two days, Friday 9th April 2010 and Saturday 10th. The first day (Friday), an older guy was behind the bar and was very helpful and friendly. He seemed to be the owner. On the second day the coffeeshop was staffed by an aggressive bald guy who was extremely unfriendly. You could feel the negativity coming off him in waves. Later after a puff, myself and my wife were sitting trying to enjoy our mellow when the bartender dude and his 5 or 6 friends hounded us out of the shop. Shouting at us and acting very hostile as we left. They were having a right good laugh at our expense. We were perfectly nice and polite and spent our money there. We are both still completely at a loss to explain it. I suspect they do not like tourists as everybody there seemed to be a local. We will stick to the tourist coffeeshops from now on. If we had not got up an left I think there would have been a real incident.

name: Samba Kitchen
text: One of the best places in Amsterdam if you like Brazilian music, caipirinha and meat. Samba Kitchen has a nice and cozy feel to it. The times I was there they always had live music. You start with a trip to the salad bar in the back to choose your side dishes. The first time I made the mistake to go 'all out' at the salad bar...DON'T! They serve Rodizio style....which means they prepare the meat on skewers roasted above a charcoal grill and come by your table to serve you different kinds of meat.....and keep coming back till you surrender. You pay a fixed price (dessert and drinks excluded) and will have a wonderfull evening garantied. I recommend your make your reservation in advance

name: Samba Kitchen
text: Gisteren hebben we daar gegeten. Service is vreselijk. Er werkt maar 1 jongen bij het vlees. Ze laten grote groepen binnen. Uiteindelijk is alles op. Heel lang wachten voor een klein stukje vlees. Ondertussen proberen ze steeds nieuwe drank te laten bestellen. Bad service. T hey allow big groups inside. They don't have enough staff. You have to wait forever for your food. Buffet is empty in a second and it takes forever for new food. Music is from youtube. All they do is try to sell you their drinks. TERRIBLE PLACE NEVER AGAIN

name: Samba Kitchen
text: Al eerder daar gegeten en was prima, maar gister was het 1 groot drama. Hadden via de website gereserveerd, maar geen bevestiging ontvangen zoals word vermeld. Dus gebeld en we konden 20.00u terecht. Het was druk, maar gezien de eerdere bezoeken goed waren gingen we toch zitten. We moesten 20 min. wachten op drinken 2e keer uiteindelijk maar zelf gaan halen, geen sfeer te bekennen behalve chaos. Vlees bij het buffet was koud en niet lekker. De bediening was verschrikkelijk. Ze hadden teveel hooi op hun vork. Maar zeg dan simpelweg dat het vol is. Wc's waren smerig. Gammel tafeltje en stoelen en zaten niet comfortabel. Binnen ! uur zijn we weg gegaan en betaal je 27,50 pp terwijl we praktisch alles op ons bord hebben laten liggen.....dus niet gunstig voor de portomonee als je bedenkt dat we elders zijn gaan eten. Duur avondje geworden op mijn verjaardag. Een vrouw die volgens mij de eigenaresse is was er niet ik denk dat, dat er ook mee te maken zou kunnen hebben. Andere keren dat we geweest zijn was zij aanwezig en ging het goed. Erg jammer!!!!! Maar ga er niet meer naartoe en raad het niet meer aan andere mensen. Bij "DE BEIAARD" IS MIJN AVOND WEER GOEDGEMAAKT aan de Marie Heinekenplein 5-8-Amsterdam.

name: Samba Kitchen
text: Wij er zaterdag gaan eten en hebben het restaurant langs internet gevonden, de verwachtingen waren hoog. Het was er koud binnen, er ging een koppel weg door de kou, muziek komt van een klein tv toestel dus niet live zoals op de site staat. het eten was voorzien van een uitgedroogde vel. Het enige dat goed was is het vlees aan spiezen en de kok die heel vriendelijk is. Bediening onder nul en voor slecht eten meer dan 80 euro neertellen neeeeeeeeeeeeeee nooit meer. PS Wij gaan meerdere malen per jaar naar Brazilie en dit is een heel slecht voorbeeld van hoe het kan zijn. Een regelrechte afknapper.

text: Taste before you serve! Service was quite hectic as it was one of the first nice days of the year. We we seeded on the terras and were having a good time. The starters were good, the baby squid in a Bologese sauce was tender and a properly seized portion, the salad was ok. It all went wrong with the main courses, both dishes were over salted, one was still ok(veal with truffle sauces), the other, tagiatelle with lobster the latter was fine, but the accompanying tagiatelle was so salt it was uneatable. Of course this can happen but when telling the waiter it was not ok his reaction appalling "ok, I will tell the chef maybe later when he is not so busy". No excuses of any kind. For me despite the good starters (and desert) never again.

name: Angry Chicken
text: This is a quirky little fast food place that sells Korean fried chicken. We tried the So So Angry Chicken and the Sexy Chicken. The chicken pieces weren't perfectly fried, but they were good enough for an expat who's craving fried chicken. The sauces were pretty tasty, but the So So Angry sauce was basically not spicy at all (certainly not the "extra spicy" that describes the sauce on the menu). Next time I will definitely try the Furious Chicken. The french fries were fantastic, some of the best that I've had in Germany. The sweet potato fries were actually fried thin ribbons of sweet potatoes, but regardless were quite delicious and crunchy.

name: Unique Berlin Events Ltd.
text: Wir haben das Team von unique berlin events zur Organisation unserer Firmenweihnachtsfeier (230 Personen in der Kalkscheune) im Dezember 2012 gebucht...Fazit der Kollegen/innen und Gesch√§ftsf√ºhrung: grandios und ph√§nomenal! Neben der mobilen Cocktailbar wurden die G√§ste mit einem sehr guten Essen verw√∂hnt. Das gro√üe Highlight war das Casino, zur Einstimmung darauf gab es einen Live-Act einer Musical-Darstellerin! Die Planung und Vorbereitung verlief mit einer gro√üen Begeisterung und einem Ideenreichtum auf das man selten trifft! Alle Abstimmungen konnten auf kurzem Weg und unkompliziert getroffen werden. Am Tag der Veranstaltung konnte ich beobachten mit welch' einer Leidenschaft unique berlin events ihren Job macht! Es hat einfach unglaublich viel Spa√ü gemacht und es gab noch nie so viel positives Feedback aus den Reihen der Belegschaft! Veranstaltung? unique!!!

name: Unique Berlin Events Ltd.
text: Letzten Samstag habe ich mit meinem Partner den Cocktailkurs von Unique Berlin Events besucht und wir sind beide sehr heiter und zufrieden wieder rausgekommen. Wir stehen kurz vor der Er√∂ffnung einer neuen Bar/Cafes und m√∂chten auch Cocktails anbieten. Nur haben wir bisjetzt noch keine Erfahrungen mit Cocktails gesammelt. Der Kurs war der ideale Einstieg, da er die Grundlagen erkl√§rt und man viel ausprobieren kann. Am wichtigsten nimmt er einem die Scheu vor dem Cocktailmixen und gibt einem das Selbstbewusstsein, dass eigentlich jeder einen leckeren Cocktail mixen kann. Am Ende haben wir sogar eine Shoppingliste bekommen, welche uns als Gewerbetreibende besonders hilft richtig einzukaufen. Alles in allem ein sehr lohnender Abend, welcher gleichermassen informativ und spassig war. Sehr, sehr empfehlenswert.

name: Unique Berlin Events Ltd.
text: Wir haben am letzten Freitag den Cocktailkurs von Unique Berlin Events Ltd. besucht und waren super zufrieden!!! Nach der Theorie: Wo kommt der Cocktail her? Was braucht man? Was muss man beachten? ging es an die Praxis. Cocktails selber mixen mit den Tipps von einem Profi!!! Die Kursunterlagen, mit den wertvollen Informationen, kamen noch in der selben Nacht per Email. Die Atmosph√§re locker. Die Veranstalter freundlich und kompetent! Der Kurs hat uns sehr viel Spass gemacht und der n√§chsten Cocktailparty Zuhause steht nichts mehr im Wege :)

name: Unique Berlin Events Ltd.
text: Wir haben unsere Hochzeit mit Unique Berlin Events gefeiert und es war einfach traumhaft perfekt! Alles wurde unseren W√ºnschen entsprechend angepasst, wir wurden die ganze Zeit sehr nett beraten und jede Idee von uns wurde angenommen und durchgef√ºhrt. Ich habe sogar extra lilafarbene Scheinwerferblenden f√ºr den Raum bekommen, weil ich so gern alles in lila haben wollte! :) Ich kann wirklich nicht genug loben: die Dekoration, die Frau Schmieder-Jordan √ºbernommen hat, h√§tte ich mir sch√∂ner nicht vorstellen k√∂nnen. Dabei hat sie meine W√únsche ber√ºcksichtigt und alles vorher per Email und in Gespr√§chen mit mir abgesprochen. Der von Unique Berlin Events empfohlene Caterer war unglaublich gut und preiswert! √úberhaupt war das ganze Preis-Leistungs-Verh√§ltnis einfach stimmig; wir konnten in ganz Berlin nichts preiswerteres finden, und das obwohl es so eine rauschende Hochzeit war! Nicht zu vergessen die Cocktails: eine riesengro√üe Auswahl, alkoholische und nichtalkoholische, die unseren G√§sten den ganzen Abend √ºber angeboten wurden, ohne dass dies die Getr√§nkepauschale teurer gemacht hat! EInfach nur gro√üartig, unsere G√§ste waren begeistert. Und super geschmeckt haben sie auch. Ich hab wirklich noch nie jemanden so schnell Cocktails zubereiten sehen wie Herrn Schmieder. Also insgesamt ein gro√ües Lob, ich kann Unique Berlin Events einfach jedem empfehlen, ein super Team, tolle Ideen, Beratung, Service, Durchf√ºhrung, perfekt! Wir hatten unsere Traumhochzeit, best√§tigt von all unseren G√§sten; ein ganz gro√ües Dankesch√∂n!!!

name: Ristorante Ciao Italia
text: Schon l√§ngere Zeit hatten wir √ºberlegt, einmal diesem "Restaurant" einen Besuch abzustatten, da es in der direkten Umgebung liegt und die Preise recht annehmbar sind. Am heutigen Sonntag hatten wir keine Lust zu kochen und entschlossen uns im "Ciao Italia" zu essen...leider...Aufgrund der niedrigen Preise und der sehr umfangreichen Speisekarte hatten wir uns schon keine gro√üen Erwartungen gemacht, dass es einen extravaganten Service und delizi√∂seste Speisen geben k√∂nnte...Wir entschlossen uns draussen zu essen, da das Wetter noch recht mild war. Die Speisekarte besteht aus ettlichen Tex-Mex-Speisen, den √ºblichen, italienischen Verd√§chtigen wie Pizza, Pasta, Salate, einige deutsche Gerichte sowie auch Straussenfleisch, K√§nguruh and so on... Wir bestellten eine gro√üe Cola, ein Ginger Ale, einmal die Quesadillas mit Champignons und ein Schnitzel "Bella Italia". Als der Kellner das Besteck brachte war schnell klar, dass er wohl nicht aus dem Gastro-Gewerbe kam, denn zumindest das Besteck richtig eindecken k√∂nnen sollte man k√∂nnen...Die Cola schmeckte so schal wie bei den bekannten Fast-Food-Ketten und das Essen...naja, sagen wir mal f√ºr den Preis ist es ok...also Curry-Wurst-Buden-Niveau...wie man an dem Schnitzel, welches sich als ein zu lange frittiertes Kotelette entpuppte, deutlich merken konnte...Wie schon so oft in diesem Sommer wollte das Wetter auch heute abend nicht auf unserer Seite sein und es fing an zu sch√ºtten wie aus F√§ssern! Erst fanden wir das gar nicht so schlimm, das Prasseln auf den kleinen, √ºbelriechenden T√ºmpel der direkt an die Terasse angrenzt war ja auch ganz nett...doch dann wurde der Regen immer st√§rker und wir mussten weiter in die Mitte der Terasse r√ºcken...Fataler Fehler!!! Die angeblich, automatische Markise, die sich laut Kellner-Auskunft, automatisch bei starkem Wind √∂ffnet ( aber nur eine von vier Markisen, komische Automatik^^) wurde der Gast am Nebentisch von dem herablaufenden Wasser durchn√§sst sowie unser Essen und unsere Getr√§nke mit Regenwasser wieder aufgef√ºllt wurden...wir gingen rein und beschwerten uns, zumindest eine Entschuldigung hatten wir erwartet....aber wir wurden recht unh√∂flich gefragt, warum wir √ºberhaupt draussen sassen und nicht durch den Platzregen in das Lokal mit unserem Essen und Getr√§nken ins Lokal gerannt w√§ren...es gab eine Diskussion unter den Kellnern und dem Gesch√§ftsf√ºhrer (der mit uns allerdings nicht reden wollte und auch nur den Kellner fragte, warum wir √ºberhaupt draussen waren...) zum Schlu√ü (nach ca. 10min rumstehen) wurden wir gefragt was wir jetzt √ºberhaupt wollten, man h√§tte alles ja schon eingebont und somit k√∂nne man uns eh keinen Nachlass geben (√§√§√§hm...ja...so eine Kasse hat ja keine Stornotaste oder √§hnliches...) und f√ºr den Regen k√∂nnen sie ja nichts, hatten wir die Faxen dicke, haben bezahlt und sind immer noch hungrig gegangen...Die bezahlten 22,20‚Ç¨ sind zwar nicht die Welt aber f√ºr den Abend, den Service und das Essen immer noch zuviel. Ich hatte dem Kellner noch versucht zu erkl√§ren, dass es klar ist, dass sie nichts f√ºr den Regen k√∂nnen aber zumindest die G√§ste darauf hinweisen, dass die Markise bei dem Regen trotzdem ge√∂ffnet wird und sie ihren Kram in Sicherheit bringen m√ºssen oder eben ins Lokal reingehen sollten wenn sie nicht nass werden wollen. Fazit: Ciao Italia wird uns definitiv nie mehr sehen und auf keinen Fall weiterempfohlen!

text: A mexican restaurant run by indians?!? Epic fail, you would at least expect the spicyness of the indian dishes but the food is disappointingly conceptless. I had an Enchilada Pollo which came on hot plate looked reasonable. The size of the portion is bit too much for me and the seasoning, well not even salt and pepper made it to horrible dish. The beans... no comment on that, the enchilada roll was dry and tasteless although the texture was right. The veggie rice as a side dish has nothing to on that plate but the biggest mistake was not serving a reasonable amount of sauce to it. The menu is like a 100 pages which is just bad enough alone. The draught beer and the service is okay the waiters are kind but this place needs a revamp and a mexican chef.

name: Quepasa Mexicana
text: Trying to find decent Mexican food in Berlin is a never ending quest. We'd heard mixed review on this place but decided to see for ourselves. The chips and salsa/guac/oniony sour cream app was on par with an El Torritos style restaurant - totally decent but not mind blowing. I had the chicken quesadilla - never have I seen so much meat in a quesadilla, ever. It was good quality white meat, tender but not quite flavored for Mexican food, the tortilla was really good. My husband got the burrito con carne and again good but rather bland as far as anything close to Mexican flavors but in a pinch worth a try IF you aren't too picky. Got the flan for dessert, fairly certain it was a pre-made flan that you can pick up at the store, again a little bland. The waiters were very un-German-like regularly checked in, cleared empty plates - it was quite nice! We also got a free shot at the end of the meal, another nice surprise.

name: Restaurante El Vell Sarri√†
text: My wife and I decided to celebrate our 11 year wedding anniversary here after hearing so many great things about their "Arros" dishes. We were quite excited to go and had high expectations. Our experience: It is true that their "Arros" is quite good. Also, the interior is offers up old school Catalan authenticity and charm. BUT apart from that, there is little else to be desired from this experience. In particular, the service was negligent and slow and our starter was late, soggy and insultingly basic considering the 12,50 Euro price. As well, they do a (seemingly intentional) poor job explaining that their "Arros" pricing is per person and NOT the final cost of the dish. Not to mention, they padded our bill by charging us for bread we didn't ask for and doubling our coffee and dessert order. I've seen better wine lists too. Had we not paid any attention to the bill we would have spent almost 15 Euros more. The staff (including the owner) was, at best, mildly apologetic for their "mistake". They definitely got a piece of my mind at the register, but unfortunately I left feeling very annoyed and like the romance and enthusiasm had been robbed from me. I doubt I will return.

name: Osteria Merope
text: For 30 years I've been driving past Carrara and finally decided to make the 10-minute detour off the A-12, and it was well worth the stopover. A beautiful town with buildings, mountain views, piazzas and sculpture dominated by, you guessed it, the local marble. But the most pleasant surprise was discovering Osteria Merope. A comfortable and friendly ambience, with superb regional specialties at reasonable prices. We were greeted by the owner who explained the menu in great detail, and gave us a history of the restaurant and its place in the town. We treated ourselves to all four courses, sharing the generous portions. It was one of the best dining experiences I've had and I will return for sure.

name: McDonald's Belgrove House
text: Never Again. Dirty, Dumb and Dull. Usually, apart from not being comprehended at all by the staff - probably the owner's family - , large parts of my order are simply omitted, due to insolence . . . They don't even bother asking what kind of sauces you would like - You know; The ones YOU PAYED FOR !?! - although, trying to peddle you their fries, seems to be quite manageable. Today, I've had enough. Upon ordering my usual Big Mac with a small Side Salad (which they didn't have - or ever seem to do), I went for a simple Cheeseburger. After the usual 5-7 Minute Wait, I went home, not only to find my Big Mac squished, beyond recognition or saving (because of the rough manner it was packed), but also a big black LUMP of tallowy, soapy (!!) OVEN GREASE, positioned neatly inside the middle of the Cheeseburger's bun. By 'inside' I do not mean that there was something on the meat- or cheese-side, but pressed INTO the top bun during toasting. Probably a remnant that fell down off one of the, obviously NOT so CLEAN, Kitchen Appliances. Today they have LOST yet another Customer. There's a saying, but it involves Kings, not Pigs ! Maybe GBK for the next fast-food craving...although JUNK Food is called thusly for a Good Reason, my Friends!

name: Bombay Nights
text: Firsts things first I NEVER get compelled to write reviews but in this cash I felt I must. After stumbling upon this restaurant after having a couple of drinks around West Hampstead I didn't really know what to expect. There was a couple of people eating and their meals looks pretty good so we went in. Instantly we were greeted by a chap who simply couldn't do more for us, he sorted out a lovely table in the back back the bar and gave us 2 halves of cobra on the house! We skipped starters and I went for the Tandorri chicken and my friend went for the Phal (super hot curry). Both were delicious and the Tandorri was done to perfection, succulent with crisped bits that tasted so good. We ordered a chilli keema naan bread and that was also excellent. -Service -Food -Atmosphere -Price All 5 stars. Will definately be back

name: Dim T
text: Some time ago, a Scottish friend of mine told me if he ever grew tired of his job, he'd start a business by buying a mobile deep fat fryer and wheeling it around Glasgow, with all foodstuff accepted to be coated in crispy batter. I was reminded of this at Dim T, where every opportunity was taken to batter the life out of the seafood dishes, and anything else the fryer could be put use to. I'm not sure how my arteries felt after a trip to Dim T, but I doubt they're happy with me. This cramped pan-Asian restaurant has a lot of heavy dishes and not much in flavour. Almost every dish was greeted with a collective shrug of "It's ok," in that wonderfully understated British way that indicates everything is far from ok. Salads were bland, katsu curries were bland, crispy battered seabass fillets in a three flavour sauce elected to skip two of the three flavours and compensate with extra batter. Prawns and squid both suffered the same fate as the battery charge grew longer. All in all, a meal that would be an excellent introduction to Asian food for people who don't like the cuisine and have no intention of ever eating it again. All this could just about be forgiven if the experience was fun. Wedged into a table not designed for a large party, much of the meal was taken up with establishing elbow etiquette. By the end, we were desperate to leave but this too was delayed by 15 minutes as the staff struggled to work out who was owed what. Normally the diner's hard work comes at the bill stage, while the restaurant puts their sweat and toil into the meal. I'm not sure I like the role reversal.

name: Sacro Cuore Pizza
text: It's a shame I have to give a 3 star to this place (same thing that happened to me with its counterpart Santa Maria in Ealing, where my experience was worse if possible). So, let's review the good stuff first. The pizza. It's very good. Dough, taste, the way it's cooked, I mean, really, you can't complain - To get better you only have to go to Napoli (where I am from, by the way) and get fresher ingredients (for obvious reasons: it's local ingredients). Considering we're in London, I could give this pizza a 4/4.5 out of 5. And that's the only reason why this place is getting a 3 star, otherwise it'd have got much less. Also good was the waitress; at Santa Maria (instead) I was treated like I was doing them a favour by eating there. Now, let's go on the bad stuff. This bad stuff are things that will probably not affect an English speaker eating there. It will probably affect an Italian speaker to a certain level. But it really gets into you if you are a Neapolitan like I am. Half of the music played in background by this place represent the worst part of the Neapolitan culture; which I can't deny, but I also don't like and by far prefer they myriad of positive aspects of the Neapolitan culture instead. While I was eating my delicious pizza with my wife, I had to cope with "Cornutone" by Squallor, a song in Neapolitan language full of swearwords and sexual vulgarity. To follow, songs belonging to the so-called "neo-melodic" genre, which are inspired (and funded) by criminality and often speak of such (more or less explicitly, depending on the song). Much better would it have been if they'd have stuck with classics like "Torero" (by the worldwide known artist Renato Carosone), which was also part of the playlist yesterday night. I don't want to get into the personal taste or life of the people that own/run the place, by I really don't think that's the kind of stuff you should be playing in a restaurant.

name: Sacro Cuore Pizza
text: Sacro Cuore is a nice and light little resaurant near Kensal Rise Overground station. The kitchen is in one corner of the restaurants, so if you are really interested in food, you can easily peak over the chefs' shoulders. For some reason, I do not know exactly why, this place reminds me a little bit of Pizza East - which is probably not a bad thing. They have a small outside seating area, which seems to be drinking and waiting area, as there are no tables. Whatever this is for, it looks nice and with one entire front open, it ensures a nice breeze on a warm summer's day. When I was there for dinner on a Saturday evening, Sacro Cuore was quite busy with a mixed crowd. I really liked the atmosphere. But I must say, depending on your mood and how fussy you are, you could probably find a number of faults with the pizza. You might find the pizza too thin, a little bit burnt and too soft and soggy at the same time, or the toppings too sparsely, and while I would not disagree that this was probably not the best pizza in my life, I simply liked it the way it was. And it was huge as well; a bit smaller would do for me. I had a white wine with my pizza and must say, I also quite liked it. You have not much choice if you order by the glass, actually, you can only order their house wine, but when the house wine tastes fine, I am happy with that. For dessert, the Nutella pizza was very tempting, but after my Pizza Bufala, I could not have another pizza, so I went instead for some ice cream. Sacro Cuore serve Oddono's (http://www.oddonos.com/) ice cream - I am not entirely sure whether I tasted it before at another place or not, I had definitely heard about it. Honestly, I found the strawberry sorbet a little bit too sweet, but the stracciatella was fabulous. All in all, I can recommend Sacro Cuore. The pizza might not be for everyone, but it's a lovely little and buzzy restaurant that's worth a visit. And when you have emptied your plates, you could enjoy a little walk in the leafy and suburban neighbourhood that feels so different from central London, despite actually being in the middle of zone 2.

name: TAP Coffee
text: Pretty much every decent Coffee place in London is either owed or run by Australians (or New Zealanders masquerading as Australians :-). TAP Coffee is no exception. It is decent, surprisingly, well made coffee. Why the surprise? The surprise is the care; the beans are ground *in front of you*. And not is some largish, bowl of bean; but the beans are taken out put into an appropriate cup and then ground. Yes, it takes a little longer, but the flavour is immensely better.

name: Pizza Hut Delivery
text: I am not one to complain and in most cases I am very tolerant of most people and also when shopping I understand that most people are under alot of pressure to deliver.However, I visited the take away Pizza Hut store in Southall on the 8 August. I was served by a young female lady. I was just so surprised as to how rude, unhelpful and impolite she was. I was even more shocked to see that she was even allowed to be on the counter with her attitude. She had no patience nor could she be bothered explaining to customer clearly when taking there orders and was completely uninterested in trying to explain to me, or the customers after me the menu. She wheeled the list off to everyone that attended so fast, considering that a majority of the local people that use the take away service are of ethnic origin and would struggle with the speed with which she spoke. I found her attitude and customer services skills completely unacceptable. She belittled everyone she spoke to, making them feel as if they were dumb. Asking her to clarify something she would get into a huff about having to repeat herself. I deal with customers myself on a daily basis and I was just so amazed that she can be allowed to carry on like, with the manager of the branch being present right besides her. She did not even explain the offer of buy one get one free clearly to me. She only gave me one pizza and the free one I had to call up to clarify why I had not received it the following day, only to be told that I was entitled to it and should have said. I too felt so intimidated by her that I did not bother asking her to clarify why she had not added the free pizza. Whilst there she had 3 customers who's order she messed up as well. She needs to be taught some manners and customer skills else she should get herself another job. I suggest that you send in one of your mystery shoppers if you have any and get them to get an experience of how she deals with them !!! I think I can vote this as "The worst experience of my life, with dealing with a purchase !!!!" Pizza was pretty naff as well.

text: I discovered this bistro through Groupon and had an amazing time with my two friends! We're tried the specials and loved each one of them, we ended up sharing each others as we enjoyed them so much. Definitely will be back, Groupon or not!

name: Goode & Wright
text: Dreadful. My friends wanted a gathering so got groupon vouchers separately but at slightly different time slots so we could eat together. Managed to do so, but the attitude of the waiter was so terrible when he found out we were actually same group of people. He even tried to provoke us to leave his restaurant - I was tempted to but my other friends arrived early and already ordered. We had also been looking forward to that dinner until we met him. I had never ever met any ruder waiter in my whole life. I even suspect he's being a bit racist. We are all Asians and not very aggressive. He said he's concerned with the atmosphere when a big group is dining, but come on, a table of Europeans beside us was even louder than us. Did he ever say anything about it? Also, if you don't like people making use of Groupon to have group gathering - don't register with it. Anyway, totally rubbish.

name: Goode & Wright
text: So nice to be looked after! I bought for a second time a Groupon voucher couple of weeks ago and decided to use it with my girl friend for our 4 years Anniversary night out. We had a lovely table next to the kitchen and the Maitre d' was just adorable. Jimmy - maitre d' - even swap our glass of wine including in the voucher for 2 glasses of bubbly for our special celebration. It really make us feel special. Thanks you so much. We didn't expected that much.

name: Goode & Wright

I had to try three times to get through although it rang avery time. When they answered they said that my booking was not valid and that "the booking system is just an automatic thing". A very rude member of the staff said he might be able to accommodate us tomorrow for lunch but they will not give us the free glass of wine included in the voucher. I asked why. name: Solly's
text: Insanely expensive for what it is. Went to sit down, nobody in restaurant, and the price for a shawarma is 17.50 Pounds, like $30 for a shawarma! (170 Danish Kroner). Insane! So, step to the right to the take-away and eat at the window on stools, save 20 Pounds! Still pricey, but worth it due to the quality shawarma (we got Lamb and Chicken) I had the chicken shawarma in a Pita with some salads, my wife had the lamb (excellent) on a plate. Even though there's NOBODY in the restaurant, since nobody in their right mind would pay those prices, you can't eat in the restaurant, only at the window. Bottom line, don't eat there, just take-away and keep the change in your pocket. If Solly really gave a crap, he'd read all the reviews, fire the staff and re/build a great business. Instead, great food with bad service and bad reviews, which is the worst thing you could ask for!

text: Harrison's is a lovely local shop with a good selection of tempting food and boos. There is something for everyone from top quality wine to very reasonably priced 2 for ¬£12 bottles of wine. They also have a good selection of local ales and I love the cured meats and pate.

name: Harrison's
text: If you love good wine, cheese and meats, you have to give this place a try. I have been using it since it opened for everything from dinner parties, drinks and weektime lunches. I don't know a lot about wine and the staff are really personable and knowledgeable about the products, in a welcoming way. The food is always interesting, and their Chorizo and Salami's are to die for! I have really enjoyed trying new things and learning about the different cheese's and wines, and the shop is great for that. I would also recommend their wine and cheese tastings, as I always feel like an expert when I leave!

name: Harrison's

Also we had to wait for our food for a very long time. Too long in my opinion.

text: The food is brilliant and very authentic! Lovely and staff were very very nice. Recommend to all who like Italian food!

name: Lacantina
text: My partner and I popped in to try it out. Well, from the starter to the bill, it was worth going. We're going back very very soon. Rich and Kaz.

name: Lacantina
text: Italian restaurant in Ealing La Cantina is the place to go to eat out with a style. They have fantastic service. Always helpful and ready to serve. They do fantastic food. I went there for my birthday party as well as for big family dinner. Food is just delicious. And prices for children are so good that I like to get something extra as I know I can afford to pay a bill there.

name: Lacantina
text: Me and my girlfriend we have been going to La Cantina for the past year quiet regularly. We started having some problems few months ago since they changed management. Tonight,another disappointing evening, after waiting over 2 hrs for the food to be delivered, we got the wrong pizzas and burnt too. So after sending the pizzas back to the kitchen, after another 20 mins wait,we had again 2 pizzas burnt but we both were too hungry to send them back. No contact from the waitress,to find out how the meal was. So when she came and collect the plates and she saw half pizza still on it she said:"was it burn again?!" Obviously as you could see the black crust still on the plate. No apologies,no discount,just a card for a free pizza for next visit,which it is never going to happen. I do understand that they are trying to make money out of the business,but I feel ripped off when the product is not as good as it used to be. We always used to go there because the staff was really friendly,and the pizzas and pasta with a lots of fillings like you have it in Italy; now you can bear recognize what you have ordered when the food gets to the table, and the staff isn't bothered at all, and the Italian manager either:he came to collect the payment with the PDQ machine,never said a word,no eye contact,nothing...he just walked off with my card!!!? They have also started to do home deliveries which i don't really understand the point when they can't even get the eating in done properly,on top of the fact that it was the main cause of delayed the eating in service (they had to give a free pizza to a table nxt to ours cause they've starting to moan about the waiting time,and one of the managers was dealing with a complaint on the phone with a guest who had a portion of chicken missing from her home delivery order)... Well, after celebrating lots of important dates for us and for our family we will def NOT gonna come back there again,especially after seeing the bill: a coke was free cause of the inconvenient caused!!! Paid for the full bill,and ripped off the "voucher" for the free pizza! You guys def need the money more the me if you keep working like that,you def gonna loose lots of business!!!! Good Luck

Nice and spacious with a good selection of restaurant type food for an excellent gastropub. Came back a week later and had a surprisingly nice bottle of white wine ( I'm usually a red drinker). Plus the staff were friendly and courteous. Also saw the biggest scotch egg I've ever seen.

The other branches are always very busy with lines thronging out the door, so take advantage of this one before it becomes too well known! As with all the Pilpel's they come around and give you a free falafel whilst you wait - service like that with food this good, you'll be returning before you know it :) *I haven't actually been around all of London to taste every single falafel pita so I _could_ potentially be wrong.

name: Pilpel

name: Tudor Barn Eltham
text: Great food, nice place, good service!

name: Tudor Barn Eltham
text: This is one of the most memorable dining experiences I have had. I was sent here on my birthday by my daughter who had obtained a deal through Groupon for a Tudor feast. My husband and I chose a meat feast, and wow this was absolutely gorgeous. The choice was perfection in itself, beautifully served on wooden shelves (which incidentally I have copied for my table at home). Everything was cooked just right so my compliments go out to the chef. The lunch time service was excellent with every consideration to supply us with a selection of drinks and keep the courses coming at just the right intervals. There is no doubt that this place is worth a visit and what a great place for a wedding or Christmas party! In fact we are so impressed that we have booked again to visit this Wednesday to try out the Tudor fish feast and we are bringing along a couple of friends for another birthday! The only downfall is the lack of parking, although there are plenty of free parking spaces in the surrounding area. But why bring the car at all when Eltham station is practically opposite. At least we can all have a drink.

name: Tudor Barn Eltham
text: I have visited this place on several occasions through the last 4 years and each time it gets better. They now offer draft beers which they were not allowed to do because of the license restrictions. The food is impeccable. Would highly recommend even for afternoon tea and cake.

name: Tudor Barn Eltham
text: Hidden Gem! really nice food, a lovely setting by the moat. Quite pricey for the location. Recommend the quails eggs and tuna steaks. They take taste card too which is a plus. Waitress was realy nice too.

name: Tudor Barn Eltham
text: Great suroundings great food well worth a visit for a special occasion

name: Tudor Barn Eltham
text: It's not so bad - probably one of the better venues in the Eltham area, and certainly better than most chain restaurants. "Bar Snack" hamburger (with cheese and bacon) contained plenty of decent meat and extras (lettuce, dill pickle, tomato, some kind of tomato relish etc.), but the bun wasn't up to the job and had fallen apart by the time I got halfway through the burger. "Hand cut" chips were undercooked and in short supply. "Coke" came in a small glass and almost certainly from a soda fountain. Dessert was passable, but whipped cream was of the aerosol variety. Service was slow (we did turn up just as the restaurant was opening) but friendly enough. Bizarrely, the outside seating by the moat is non-smoking.

name: Greekylicious
text: A real taste of Greece in Palmers Green. The food is very reasonably priced and tasty, especially the Greek salad. This is not a kebab as you would normally expect, it is a traditional Gyros. The portion size is more than enough, any larger and consider yourself a pig. Give it a try, you will not regret it.

name: Greekylicious
text: Decided to try this new place as to open a kebab shop in palmers green you have to have something good as by law, every other shop is a kebab shop. Has to be good right? Put in a big order of over ¬£20 and boy was i disappointed. The chicken kebabs were not typically in a pita. It came in a box (take away which I wanted) with everything cut up so you don't get a full pita, the salad included NO greens. Literally, several slices of tomato and onion. Flavourless cheap chicken meat and I could count how many chips I had in my plate. If you can count how many chips you have in your plate (7) then it's a big fat zero for me. The portion size wouldn't even satisfy the stomach of a smurph. Sorry Greekylicious, you are up against a load of competition which offer a range of value for money, bigger portion size and more than 7 chips. P.S. The haloumi is a whopping ¬£3.50. I could buy nearly 3 for that much.

name: Arkay Chilled Foods
text: I have done a lot of travelling in my time, and sampled fine foods in over 30 countries, above all i appreciate a good mature cheddar cheese, there are many brands and flavours out there, some with zing and bite others smooth and full flavoured, but until now i had not come across "Calveley Mill Arkay Mature Cheddar". If anyone out there wants to be put OFF cheese for LIFE, try "Calveley Mill Arkay Mature Cheddar" Today i was put in the horrible situation where my fianc√©e cooked me a lovely spag bol, and the supermarkets were shut so i dashed to the nearest corner shop and picked up a block of "Calveley Mill Arkay Mature Cheddar" (@ ¬£3 for just 400g), i got home just in time and grated the "Calveley Mill Arkay Mature Cheddar" onto my delicious dinner and started eating (I was very hungry). First i stopped chewing........ a few moments went by that felt like eternity........ my jaw dropped...... (i was in some kind of shock) the food fell out of my mouth, as the error of my ways slowly dawned on me.... could this be true?? was it really happening to me?? I mean, you hear of terrible things happening to other people, but you never expect it to happen to you. Unfortunately my fears weren't unfounded, what i had just done was to attempt to eat the worst mature cheddar, in not just the world, or our galaxy, but the entire universe!!! Now, I have never tried to chew the feet off a rotting cadaver, but if i ever had to choose between the two, I know which one I would opt for. Words cant describe what i went through (let alone the amount of toothpaste mouthwash and bleach i had to use) I proceeded to offer my dinner to my golden Labrador Molly, she is a lovely girl (sometimes eats her own poo, bless her) I never knew a dog could give a death stare, but she did, and growled and walked off. Sadly Molly and I don't get along any more. Thank you for the opportunity to make myself heard, and hopefully it will save some palates out there. I will sooner die of hunger than to eat your cheese again, needless to say I have had it incinerated as I would hate some poor rats to drag it out of the bin and taste it. Please stop producing this cheese today, kindest regards nick.

name: The Co-operative Food
text: Ten minutes before close and you want to go and get something quick? They'll say they're closed and shout at you pointing at an analog clock that reports the time incorrectly. Even after you muscle your way through and get your jar of "food", you notice the till receipt still shows that there's a good five minutes left. It's a nice clean store, but the people there are so detached and grumpy that it compels people across the street to Budgens.

name: Nando's The Brunswick
text: Management seriously lacks integrity. My incident was non food related but if Nandos Brunswick can act like this in one matter, why would they be any better in their food processes. I left my phone behind on the table and called Nandos twenty minutes later once I had noticed. In spite of the fact that the table WOULD HAVE HAD TO HAVE BEEN CLEANED before the next customers sat there, I was told nothing had been found. Ok I thought - let me ask for the person who cleaned the table and ask them. But the manageress said she could not reveal who cleaned my table. If you had nothing to hide, and frankly if you just wanted to be helpful, you would have had no hesitation in calling that staff member over and asking them if they had found anything. I was not accusing anyone at this stage of having taken my phone; I just wanted the opportunity to ask the relevant member of staff what they had seen when they were clearing the table. Being denied this simple piece of information I suspect foul play. Shocked by this (lack of) response, I asked if I could see the CCTV. Absolutely not said the manageress, informing me I'd have to submit a police request. I understand this is normal criminal procedure but again if you wanted to be helpful and felt you had nothing to hide (let alone wanted to see if your staff were honest) you would have complied with my request. I will be taking this matter as far as I can to ensure people are aware of the lack of integrity you have showed.

name: Nando's The Brunswick

name: Cinnamon
text: Food was average. Nothing special like we had assumed taking into consideration all the accolades this venue has supposedly gained. I assume not. Venue was tired and lacked any warmth. Had a very unpleasant business diner. Was meant to showcase colleagues from Norway the finest Indian Meal on offer but went the opposite way. Came out feeling dormant and embarrassed. Its a restaurant, a licensed restaurant but missing all the good wines and lacks the authentic feel of curry. Furnished more like pizzeria then Indian. Disappointed.

name: Cinnamon
text: Above average but nothing to rave about. Had dinner at this restaurant with a big group of friends. The deal is reasonable very much on par with all the other restaurants near by. I tried 4 of the main dishes and all the curries were nice. If you are looking for a decent curry where you can bring your own drinks this place is okay.

name: Cinnamon
text: The main draw to any curry house on Brick Lane is the food - the decor is rarely anything to shout home about, but the food is where it all lies. And at Cinnamon, they more than deliver. Every curry I've had there was nothing more than divine, and I would recommend it to anyone with a passing interest in curry. The staff are friendly - even if they keep their red wine in a place that's a little too cool. It also has the problem of any Brick Lane restaurant with the touters outside - trying to bring you in. A good chance to get some extras if you have a silver tongue, but those unprepared will find them intimidating.

name: Cinnamon
text: A very good night out at the cinnamon. Definitely will be back and recommend to anyone.

name: Cinnamon
text: Words are not enough to describe the sheer horror of dining at this establishment. After being promised a discount at the door they refused to provide this and literally grabbed my hands and pulled me off my chairs to get me out. Food was awful and I had complained about this earlier which is probably why they were soo tempermental. dirty greasy premises with waiters always giving the evil eye. Avoid.

name: The Speaker
text: If you're in SW1 and looking for a good real ale pub I'd recommend you try this place. The landlord, Dennis, is usually in residence - always a good sign of a pub when the landlord is evident. This is a wonderful antidote to the now depressingly common chain pubs all over London, with real character. They're also very proud of the fact they have no fruit machines or piped music - and rightly so. Really good selection of interesting and unusual beers on tap, which seems to change constantly. This is one of the few places in London I've been able to find mild, and they have a number of different themed beer festivals at different times of the year. All of that and it's a proper, genuine tradition pub with an unspoilt interior.

name: The Speaker
text: This is the perfect pub for me and my friends. We try to visit the Speaker at least once a week and enjoy a couple of beers there.

name: The Speaker

text: Yo! Fresco is tasty and I recommend you to try it. It is a popular Japanese refreshment drink and is worth a try. In the restaurant they have over 80 dishes and I believe that you will find your favourite one there. Try also the Salmon Teriyali- it is simply mouth-watering. I like it a lot, because the grilled salmon is cooked in a sweet, sticky soy based sauce.

name: Yo! Sushi
text: Love this place... best place for fast and easy sushi. not the best sushi chain in the world, but very good anyway. The hot dishes are also brillian and you order from the staff. Fun atmosphere and quick...

name: Yo! Sushi
text: Yo Sushi is one of the oldest sushi chains around. This meant that a few years ago, when the concept of picking sushi from a conveyor belt was first introduced in 1997, the restaurant probably had the status of most original and trendiest dining experience in all of London. Today, with the opening of a new sushi place every day, Yo Sushi has struggled to remain on top of its competitors. The main explanation behind this downfall is the quality of the sushi as well as, in my opinion, the interior design of all its restaurants. Firstly to the sushi: average quality, plain tasting and resultantly overpriced. The interior design: white, cold and plastic. No warmth or comfort whatsoever.

name: Yo! Sushi
text: it has had a lot of bad press, but when you are drunk and need a guilty pleassure then this is the one!! always you know what you get and it ia all good

name: Yo! Sushi
text: As most people who acutally enjoy sushi, I avoid YoSushi like the plague. However living on a budget and as my friend wanted to go, I went. For once, the service was really good, quick and unobtrusive. If you can, order dishes only, 'cos that way at least it's fresh. here you can see them working, which is good. The main plus is 25% off for students everyday. So a ¬£20 meal goes down to ¬£15. That's 6 plates and a japanese tea. Avoid the cheaper plates which you don't know, they be very bland and overseasoned.

name: Doctor Espresso Caffetteria
text: The Best Espresso, perfectly made by a 1959 Gaggia's

name: Doctor Espresso Caffetteria
text: Try the Ciabatta , mozzarella and Parma ham!!!

name: Doctor Espresso Caffetteria
text: Home to London's oldest working espresso machine, a lovely Gaggia lever model, Doctor Espresso Caffetteria serves up a slice of Italy directly opposite Putney Bridge tube station on the District Line. It helps that the coffee, roasted in Italy and shipped to London, is excellent, a real old-school espresso experience. However, it's not just for coffee geeks and lovers of old machinery. The coffee, which is some of the best you'll find, is backed up by some lovely Italian food: panini, calzone, pizza, pasta & salad, along with some delicious cakes and pastries. So far I've managed to sample a couple of the calzone and a couple of the cakes, all of which were delicious. Finally, Doctor Espresso Caffetteria, although small, is a great place; the decor is quirky, but well thought out and the outdoor seats are a delight in the summer. The staff, all of whom (bar one) are Italian are friendly and helpful, giving the place a very neighbourhood feel. Worth getting off the train specifically for a visit!

name: Prezzo
text: We have to say we were very disappointed with Prezzon this time around in Kingston. First time we went was in May 2010 and it was fantastic, unfortunately we didn't have a great experience this time. We had pre-booked a table for our anniversary and thought everything was going to be great but on this occaision we arrived and was told as soon as we got in the door that the chef was late arriving... strange but we could deal with that. Anyway, the place only had 8 people sitting down and most of these had already began their main meals so we thought great, not long then till being served. Well we sat down and thought the waiter was coming over so we could order some drinks - 15-20 mins later we are still sitting there and the waiter/s had walked past us about 6-7 times and hadn't said a thing. With this going on, there were still people arriving and being seated. Time went on and then a couple that had come in after us were suddenly served drinks and the same with another. By this point my very very mild mannered partner could take no more and she got her coat on and we both began to leave. On the way out, the waitress looked at us and didn't even say a word as to why we were leaving. We were disgusted. We have never experienced anything so poor. We won't be returning. So after we left we both decided to pop in to Carluccio's. We got there, was seated straight away in a packed restaurant, was served drinks 3 minutes later and was tucking into our mains in 10 minutes later. The food was the best I have had in a very long time and the waitress was very friendly and helpful. Fantastic service... Carluccio's will have my custom in future. Thanks Carluccio's!

text: Cambiata gestione - esperienza da non ripetere. Sono tornato da "Ferro e Fuoco" ad Ottobre 2013 dopo qualche mese di assenza e l'esperienza √® stata a dir poco deludente e da non ripetere assolutamente. E' un locale che ho frequentato per anni e in cui mi sono sempre trovato bene ma il cambio di gestione di Agosto 2013 (il locale ora si chiama "Fero e Foco", alla romana) evidentemente √® andato a discapito della qualit√†. Siamo andati con un'altra coppia con bambini e a parte l'accoglienza gentile la serata √® stata un vero disastro. L'antipasto "Fero e Foco" spacciato dalla cameriera come un mix di salumi, affettati e bruschiette nient'altro era che 2 piatti piccoli da antipasto con 6 fette di salumi (contate), due triangoli minuscoli di formaggio piccante ed una bruschetta fredda. Nulla a che vedere con il vecchio tagliere "Ferro e Fuoco" della gestione precedente. Prezzo: 20‚Ç¨ Abbiamo preso poi delle pizze e anche li la qualit√† del cibo √® risultata assolutamente non adeguata, tanto √® che abbiamo praticamente lasciato tutti pi√π della met√† della pizza. Prezzo medio per una pizza 9‚Ç¨ Tutto questo condito da una interminabile attesa di 1 ora e 30 minuti. Che dire se avete un buon ricordo del vecchio "Ferro e Fuoco" evitate di andare a "Fero e Foco".

name: Mez√© Bistrot
text: Passo quasi ogni sera per Via di Monteverde ed ho sempre guardato con curiosit√† l'evoluzione di questo ristorante di cucina mediterranea, aperto ormai da circa un anno. Incuriosito da un affluenza sempre maggiore ho deciso di provarlo e devo dire che il risultato √® stato molto positivo. L'arredamento del locale √® s√¨ sobrio, ma presenta al contempo una personalit√† marcata, merito sicuramente della proprietaria presente in sala. Il personale tutto √® estremamente cordiale, disponibile e sorridente, al punto da farti sentire a casa tua. A cena eravamo in due e abbiamo deciso di assaggiare un paio di Mez√© (piccole portate che precedono il pasto vero e proprio, come ad esempio l'Homous e il Babaganush) molto ben fatti devo dire. Abbiamo poi continuato il pasto con un Manzo di Istu, tipico piatto dello Sri Lanka (uno dei cuochi infatti √® cingalese) ed un Kebab al piatto di pollo e tacchino: la carne in entrambe i piatti era molto buona e saporita, in particolare nel kebab il pollo era bello croccante. Per finire mi sono concesso anche un dolce, il cannolo libanese, una specie di crepe fatta solo con acqua e farina con all'interno ricotta di pecora e succo di fiori d'arancio, a dir poco deliziosa. Lo consiglio sicuramente come posto a chiunque voglia passare una serata diversa, assaporando cibi di altre culture, in un ambiente rilassante e cordiale.

name: Al Presidente
text: To put it bluntly, DO NOT EAT HERE! Having struggled to find a decent restaurant we thought Al Presidente would be a good bet. It was fairly busy and the menu and presentation of the fresh fish in the window looked impressive, however we were fooled by the aesthetics. Once our order was taken it was down hill from there. The service was none existant, the food took an eternity to arrive, and there were no check-ups to make sure the food was good. We received the bill and noticed they had taken the liberty to add a 10% 'service' charge. We asked for them to remove it, but they refused, so we paid for our meals (minus the service charge) and left. Upon leaving, we were briefly chased down the street by a group of angry, aggressive waiters (it could have easily turned into a fight). The manager arrived, and after receiving many unpleasantries we left without paying the service charge. Should you eat here, be prepared for your holiday to be ruined.

name: Popi Popi
text: Il massimo che potevamo trovare, io e mia moglie, a Trastevere. Un locale carino e raffinato nella sua sobriet√†. Che dire dei piatti deliziosi a base di pesce, sempre fresco (si consiglia di prenotare). Il mio piatto migliore? Risotto alla crema di scampi, la "zuppa di cozze" ed il polipo farcito...le pizze poi, un impasto meraviglioso che delizia il palato, con qualsiasi variet√† di gusti e qualit√†. La matriciana poi √® eccezionale; gli straccetti alla romana; la trippa, la coda alla vaccinara, i fritti, tra cui i fiori di zucca ripieni, le olive ascolane; le birre e i vini; i dolci....insomma √® tutto buono. Volete un consiglio? Prenotate subito e non ve ne pentirete. D'estate poi √® bello mangiare all'esterno, nella piazzetta attistante la chiesa. Il servizio √® ottimo; i camerieri sempre gentili; i tempi di attesa? B√®, dipende da cosa avete ordinato, ma nei tempi giusti. I prezzi? Favolosi. Io ogni volta che sono a Roma con la mia famiglia, oramai √® diventata una tappa fissa. La consiglierei a chiunque, specialmente ai turisti che vogliono deliziare le specialit√† di Roma. name: Obik√†
text: Unlike most Americans who visit the Eternal City, we live here half the year and have for nearly two decades. We own an apartment, speak Italian fluently and dress and act in a way that is consonant with the conservative Roman ethos. Over the years, we've eaten at far more restaurants than we could ever recall and our dining experiences have, more often than not, been quite good, if not always spectacular. In past experiences at Obika, we've noted the slow and somewhat erratic service problems, but shrugged them off because the food is acceptable and the price not prohibitive. That said, over our last few visits, the service has continued to degrade until today when we experienced what unquestionably was the WORST treatment we have ever received in an Italian restaurant. Apparently, the wait staff at Obika is chosen more for their ability to strike a pose or shift some attitude than for doing the simple, if unglamorous job of taking and serving orders. While we were quickly seated at a table in the uncrowded patio, it nevertheless took more than ten minutes to receive a menu and then not with any special courtesy. I suppose we could have forgiven that long wait if we'd ever had the expectation of seeing our waiter again, but then he spent the next twenty minutes assiduously doing everything he could to avoid us and/or our vicinity. He was a very busy boy clearing off empty tables, chit-chatting with other (unoccupied) colleagues and generally looking as off-put and over-stressed as he could manage. As noted, we lasted twenty minutes in our frozen place of solitude before 'getting the idea' and making a quick, if not especially noble exit to a restaurant that actually wanted our custom.

name: Ristorante Pizzeria da Michele
text: Awesome value for your money and the food is very good. Service is courteous. After a disappointing experience with one of the restaurants near Colloseum, we decided to try a restaurant a few more blocks further and found Da Michelle. They do not have any cover charges. And they charge not much more than the supermarket for bottled water they served. We saved nearly 30% on the total bill compared to a similar dinner at one of the touristy restaurants. There are also a few gelato places nearby that charges 40% less than those near tourist sites for you to have dessert. So if you happen to stay near the Monti area, I recommend Da Michele for very good food at very reasonable prices with courteous service.

name: Zen Zoo
text: Came here for boba only because we arrived at the restaurant too late and they wouldn't serve us. The boba was decent but not soft enough. The tea flavor was very mild as well. We ordered the traditional boba milk tea and red bean milk tea. The flavors for our drinks were underwhelming. To improve on their flavors, they first need to get a stronger tea flavor. I suspect that their drinks are mild because of the French clientele they serve. Only good thing is the level of sweetness. Usually in LA, these drinks are really sweet. The drinks in Paris were on point in terms of sweetness level for me. If this is the best boba they can get in Paris, then it's worth coming back, but if there are other stores, I have yet to try them out and I hope other people will post comparisons. They speak mandarin and French.

name: Blend
text: The Cheesy at Blend is a play on the classic cheeseburger. The ingredients consist of Beef, Cheddar, bacon, homemade ketchup, fried onions, pickles, and iceberg lettuce. The burger packs a lot of promise since these ingredients typically blend very well together. However, I found that the bun was too dry and there was not as much sweet and savory juiciness that I would have expected. The beef has a complex flavor but the burger falls short of being the "melt" I imagined by a significant measure. Make no mistake that Blend does make some very good burgers; however there are better burgers to be had in Paris.

name: Blend
text: We waited a little bit for them to open and was one of the first ones inside, but the few seats filled up quickly. The burgers were awesome, and the fries and slightly sweet/spicy ketchup were good. Decent selection of some distinctly American craft beers. The only down side, in my estimation, was that the burgers could have a little more heft to them, they seem a bit dainty and small, but, in combination with the fries, it was enough to sufficiently fill me up. The staff was excellent and attentive (and spoke English!), and the restaurant was comfortable and atmospheric. Definitely would like to try it again sometime and check out the burgers I didn't try.
